        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 5:23PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Winfield, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ripley, Spencer, Winfield, Eleanor, Buffalo, Poca, Sandyville, Kenna,
Bancroft, Statts Mills, Harmony, Given, Southside, Kentuck, Liberty,
Grimms Landing, Evans, Leroy, Fairplain, and Gay.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 77 in West Virginia between mile markers 116 and 141.
Interstate 64 in West Virginia near mile marker 43.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
